<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="125" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,761,190,917]" pageId="30" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,262,638,661]" pageId="30" pageNumber="125">Remarks.</emphasis>
This group holds the species formerly treated as 
<emphasis box="[180,442,670,694]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="125">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1877" box="[180,302,670,693]" class="Insecta" family="Anthicidae" genus="Microhoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">Microhoria</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[309,442,671,694]" pageId="30" pageNumber="125" sensu="stricto">sensu stricto</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
. They are undoubtedly closely related to members of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Chevrolat" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[473,595,702,726]" class="Insecta" family="Anthicidae" genus="Microhoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis box="[473,595,702,726]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="125">M. fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group, but differ by the more conspicuous sexual dimorphism. However, it should be stated, that both modifications of metatibiae and elytral apices of males in this group are variably developed and most of the above listed species were only briefly examined or included on the basis of original descriptions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
